    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Motifs in the form of a snake, often stylized; seen in ceramics, textiles, and other works. For shapes that are sinuous but not necessarily resembling snakes, prefer "serpentine (shape)."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
